      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        " #  Car Price Prediction Model\n",
        "\n",

        "\n",
        "## Objective\n",
        "The goal of this assignment is to build the best possible regression model to predict automobile **MSRP** (manufacturer-suggested retail price) using the available car attributes.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Problem Definition\n",
        "This is a **supervised machine learning regression problem** because the target variable, MSRP, is continuous numeric data.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Who Might Be Interested in This Problem and Why?\n",
        "Several business stakeholders could be interested in this problem:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Car manufacturers** may want to understand which features most strongly influence vehicle price.\n",
        "- **Dealerships** could use the model to price inventory more accurately and identify overpriced or underpriced vehicles.\n",
        "- **Consumers** may benefit from better price transparency.\n",
        "- **Analytics teams** can use the model to support pricing strategy, forecasting, and market positioning.\n",
        "\n",
        "## What Does the Data Look Like?\n",
        "The dataset contains over 10,000 cars, where each row represents a real vehicle and its characteristics. The target variable is **MSRP**, and the remaining variables describe features such as engine performance, fuel type, size, transmission, MPG, popularity, and more.\n",
        "\n",
        "In this notebook, I will:\n",
        "1. Explore and clean the data\n",
        "2. Convert required categorical variables into numeric form\n",
        "3. Visualize important patterns\n",
        "4. Split the data into training and testing sets\n",
        "5. Train 3 simple regression models\n",
        "6. Perform forward and backward variable selection\n",
        "7. Build a final regression model\n",
        "8. Evaluate performance using **MAE, MSE, and R²**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "niI_7lJWiMRs"
      }
    },
