    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Handling Missing Values\n",
        "\n",
        "For numeric variables, I fill missing values with the median because it is less sensitive to extreme values than the mean. For this assignment, most unused categorical variables will later be dropped, so only the variables needed for modeling are kept and cleaned."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "C6aIyhQUi06x"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Identify numeric and categorical columns\n",
        "numeric_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\n",
        "categorical_cols = df.select_dtypes(exclude=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Numeric columns:\", numeric_cols)\n",
        "print(\"\\nCategorical columns:\", categorical_cols)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "8FIokstqi2rX",
        "outputId": "04d30461-64fa-4be1-b0e0-c559d272e25b"
      },
      "execution_count": 8,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Numeric columns: ['Year', 'Engine_HP', 'Engine_Cylinders', 'Number_of_Doors', 'highway_MPG', 'city_mpg', 'Popularity', 'MSRP']\n",
            "\n",
            "Categorical columns: ['Make', 'Model', 'Engine_Fuel_Type', 'Transmission_Type', 'Driven_Wheels', 'Market_Category', 'Vehicle_Size', 'Vehicle_Style']\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Fill numeric missing values with median\n",
        "for col in numeric_cols:\n",
        "    df[col] = df[col].fillna(df[col].median())"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7lc4B8ohi4nr"
      },
      "execution_count": 9,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Required Variable Conversion\n",
        "\n",
        "The instructions require:\n",
        "- **Driven_Wheels** to be converted using **OneHotEncoder**\n",
        "- **Vehicle_Size** to be converted using **OrdinalEncoder**\n",
        "- all other unnecessary categorical variables to be dropped\n",
        "\n",
        "This is necessary because regression models require numeric input variables."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YKtBhtPYi6re"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Check if required columns exist\n",
        "print(\"Driven_Wheels in columns?\", 'Driven_Wheels' in df.columns)\n",
        "print(\"Vehicle_Size in columns?\", 'Vehicle_Size' in df.columns)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "moGtieINi8iu",
        "outputId": "09d977a9-430d-4841-b998-60d7e7d52221"
      },
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Driven_Wheels in columns? True\n",
            "Vehicle_Size in columns? True\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "* OneHotEncode Driven_Wheels*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "w0kzEBXKlk-v"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# OneHotEncode Driven_Wheels\n",
        "ohe = OneHotEncoder(drop='first', sparse_output=False, handle_unknown='ignore')\n",
        "\n",
        "driven_encoded = ohe.fit_transform(df[['Driven_Wheels']])\n",
        "driven_encoded_df = pd.DataFrame(\n",
        "    driven_encoded,\n",
        "    columns=ohe.get_feature_names_out(['Driven_Wheels']),\n",
        "    index=df.index\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# OrdinalEncode Vehicle_Size\n",
        "# Logical size ordering: Compact < Midsize < Large\n",
        "vehicle_size_order = [['Compact', 'Midsize', 'Large']]\n",
        "ord_enc = OrdinalEncoder(categories=vehicle_size_order)\n",
        "\n",
        "df['Vehicle_Size_Ordinal'] = ord_enc.fit_transform(df[['Vehicle_Size']])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yHrzxyHejEdF"
      },
      "execution_count": 11,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        " Combine encoded columns with original dataframe"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zv5YZDIclpaz"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Combine encoded columns with original dataframe\n",
        "df_model = pd.concat([df, driven_encoded_df], axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Drop original encoded categorical columns\n",
        "df_model = df_model.drop(columns=['Driven_Wheels', 'Vehicle_Size'])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FqfsN8E9jG4H"
      },
      "execution_count": 12,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        " Drop all other categorical variables that are not being used"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "T_Bx16wAltA4"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Drop all other categorical variables that are not being used\n",
        "remaining_cats = df_model.select_dtypes(exclude=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\n",
        "print(\"Remaining categorical columns to drop:\", remaining_cats)\n",
        "\n",
        "df_model = df_model.drop(columns=remaining_cats)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Final shape after dropping unused categorical variables:\", df_model.shape)\n",
        "df_model.head()"
      ],
