      "source": [
        "## Model Evaluation Function\n",
        "\n",
        "This function calculates key performance metrics for a regression model, including:\n",
        "- **MAE (Mean Absolute Error):** average absolute difference between actual and predicted values\n",
        "- **MSE (Mean Squared Error):** average squared difference, which penalizes larger errors more\n",
        "- **R² (R-squared):** measures how well the model explains the variation in the target variable\n",
        "\n",
        "It also prints the results in a clean format and returns the metrics so they can be reused later for comparison."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "LsDdvipkmhOn"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def evaluate_model(y_true, y_pred, model_name):\n",
        "    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred)\n",
        "    mse = mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred)\n",
        "    r2 = r2_score(y_true, y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(f\"{model_name}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"MAE: {mae:,.2f}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"MSE: {mse:,.2f}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"R²: {r2:.4f}\")\n",
        "    print(\"-\" * 40)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return mae, mse, r2"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NF640xcQj037"
      },
      "execution_count": 23,
      "outputs": []
