        "## Interpretation of Final Model Coefficients\n",
        "\n",
        "The table above shows how each variable affects MSRP in the final regression model. Each coefficient represents the expected change in MSRP for a one-unit increase in the variable, holding all other variables constant.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Positive Impact on MSRP\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Engine_Cylinders (+10,857)**  \n",
        "  → Vehicles with more cylinders tend to be significantly more expensive.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Engine_HP (+299.77)**  \n",
        "  → Each additional unit of horsepower increases MSRP by about $300, confirming that performance strongly drives price.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **city_mpg (+623.82)** and **highway_MPG (+194.60)**  \n",
        "  → Surprisingly, higher fuel efficiency is associated with higher prices in this model, possibly reflecting more advanced or modern vehicles.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Year (+290.28)**  \n",
        "  → Newer vehicles tend to be more expensive, which aligns with expectations.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Negative Impact on MSRP\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Vehicle_Size_Ordinal (-12,412.22)**  \n",
        "  → Larger vehicles are associated with lower MSRP in this model, which may reflect how the ordinal encoding was defined or interactions with other variables.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Driven_Wheels (rear and four wheel drive)**  \n",
        "  → Rear-wheel drive (-13,929.70) and four-wheel drive (-19,951.96) show negative coefficients, which may indicate interactions with other variables rather than a true negative effect.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Number_of_Doors (-2,659.95)**  \n",
        "  → Vehicles with more doors tend to be slightly cheaper, possibly reflecting differences between luxury sports cars and standard sedans.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Popularity (-2.59)**  \n",
        "  → A very small negative effect, suggesting minimal influence on price.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Important Note\n",
        "\n",
        "Some coefficients may appear counterintuitive (e.g., drivetrain or vehicle size). This can happen due to:\n",
        "- interactions between variables\n",
        "- multicollinearity\n",
        "- encoding choices\n",
        "\n",
        "### Overall Insight\n",
        "\n",
        "The strongest drivers of MSRP in this model are **engine performance (cylinders and horsepower)** and **vehicle age (year)**. This reinforces the idea that both performance and modern features play a major role in determining car prices."
      ],
