        "However, there are several limitations:\n",
        "- The **MAE (~$20,000)** is still relatively large, indicating noticeable prediction errors\n",
        "- The **scatterplot showed poor performance for high-priced vehicles**, meaning the model struggles with luxury cars\n",
        "- The **high skewness and kurtosis** suggest strong outliers in MSRP\n",
        "- The **large condition number (~1e6)** indicates multicollinearity, which can make coefficients unstable\n",
        "\n",
        "Because of these issues, the model is useful but not highly precise.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## What do you propose as the next steps?\n",
        "\n",
        "To improve the model, the following steps are recommended:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Transform the target variable (MSRP)** using a log transformation to handle skewness and outliers  \n",
        "- **Address multicollinearity** by removing or combining highly correlated variables (e.g., Engine_HP and Engine_Cylinders)  \n",
        "- **Engineer new features**, such as interactions between performance and vehicle type  \n",
        "- **Handle outliers**, especially extremely expensive vehicles that distort the model  \n",
